werewolf is a significant piece of information, but we must be careful not to jump to conclusions. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and gather more evidence before making any decisions. I encourage everyone to continue observing the behavior of the players and sharing their observations. Let's work together to identify the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nRichard has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nRichard voted for Cyril\nCharles voted for abstain\nAaron voted for Richard\nCyril voted for Cyril\nWilliam voted for Richard\nBilly voted for Richard\nJill voted for Richard\nSherry voted for Richard\nCarol voted for Richard\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Richard has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 2,\n  \"day/night\": \"night\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Charles\",\n    \"Aaron\",\n    \"Cyril\",\n    \"William\",\n    \"Billy\",\n    \"Jill\",\n    \"Sherry\",\n    \"Carol\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, as a werewolf, it is your turn to make a kill decision.\nAlive players: Charles, Aaron, Cyril, William, Billy, Jill, Sherry, Carol\nAlive werewolves: Cyril, Billy, Carol\n\nFollow these steps to decide your action as a werewolf:\n\n1. Evaluate high-value roles. Consider if any players are likely to be a seer, witch, or guard based on their behavior and past actions. Have any players acted in ways that suggest they possess one of these powerful roles? Record your thoughts on potential high-value roles in `high_value_role_assessment`.\n2. Assess the guard's likely protection target. Based on your assumptions about high-value roles, who do you think the guard might be prote