yers and sharing their observations. Let's work together to identify the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nRichard has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nRichard voted for Cyril\nCharles voted for abstain\nAaron voted for Richard\nCyril voted for Cyril\nWilliam voted for Richard\nBilly voted for Richard\nJill voted for Richard\nSherry voted for Richard\nCarol voted for Richard\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Richard has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Cyril': 'William', 'Billy': 'William', 'Carol': 'Cyril'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Cyril', 'Billy', 'Carol']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: William\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 2 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: William, Cyril\nPlayer Cyril has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayer William has been eliminated from the game.\nAaron's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all had a peaceful night. The recent eliminations of Cyril and William are significant, and we need to stay vigilant. Cyril was supposedly a werewolf, but his elimination doesn't necessarily mean that Richard's claim was correct. We must be cautious and gather more information before making any decisions. I have been observing the behavior of the remaining players and have noticed that Charles has been quite vocal in his accusations, which might be a sign that he is trying to manipulate the group. On the other hand, Billy, Jill, Sherry, and Carol seem to be more cautious and are encouraging open discus